welcome to the second edition of the stanford seiu bargaining update in connection with stanford university page 1 issue 2 july 17 2009 from the stanford bargaining team welcome to the second edition of the stanford seiu bargaining update in connection with stanford university's contract negotiations with the service employees international union local 2007 seiu on july 7 2009 stanford and seiu began negotiations for a new collective bargaining agreement for approximately 1200 employees in schools and departments across the university including the slac national laboratory this update which will be available weekly during the course of these negotiations will provide information about ideas and interests discussed options tentatively agreed to or otherwise disposed of please disseminate the update as needed stanford and the seiu negotiations update the stanford and seiu negotiating teams met on july 14 and 16 2009 and began serious discussions regarding the mutually framed issue of securing long term quality jobs while achieving cost reductions the framing of the issue in this manner is an acknowledgment of the serious financial challenges facing the university together with the interests as expressed by the union's bargaining team the focus of the discussion was to develop a deeper understanding of the issues which underscore the respective interests and then to generate options which are defined as possible solutions targeted to address these interests on july 16 2009 a joint task force held its first meeting during this session megan davis associate vice president finance and administration land buildings and real estate presented detailed information regarding service centers and indirect cost recovery funding this information allowed participants to gain a deeper understanding of how service centers are funded definitions government regulations and the relationship between billable hours expenses and charge out rates also presenting to the team were seiu members ed ramirez paint shop and david zollo grounds who shared their thoughts as subject matter experts for their respective areas the parties will resume negotiations on tuesday july 21 2009 the stanford bargaining team the stanford bargaining team includes david a jones director employee & management services human resources ann allison marsh senior manager employee & labor relations human resources cori bossenberry director of human resources school of medicine robert carpenter director of operations buildings and grounds maintenance land buildings and real estate megan davis associate vice president page 2 issue 2 july 17 2009 finance land buildings and real estate eric montell executive director stanford dining residential and dining enterprises and larry young director of human resources slac national laboratory
